	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The shielding is probably also present to reduce emissions that could interfere with other devices. The FCC probably has fairly strict limits on what a device can put out in the RF spectrum. On the plus side, removing the coverting should allow things to run cooler inside.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


