	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />so, in other words, I'm not doing anyone any major disservice by just scrapping the RF shield?  That would save me a bunch of time when reassembling NES consoles.  I found the video output to be A OK via A/V cables, and that's all most people are set up for nowadays with hi-def TVs and all.  
<br />
<br />BTW if anyone cares, I do console repairs for Play N Trade and I basically do NES repairs out of the kindness of my heart considering what both I and the store make off of repairing newer consoles like the XBOX 360, etc.  Most people would say screw it and not bother, but I won't let salvageable systems die...ever.  I'll even try to fix worthless PSX's if I have time and there is anything I can do (unfortunately, however, a new PSX laser costs more than a whole stack of used loose systems).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
